**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.50%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>

<item instructions>
/ 1 = "Positive and negative adjectives appear in the middle of the screen and have to be sorted into the two categories above.
~nFor example, adjective 'awesome' would be sorted into the category GOOD. Adjective 'ugly' would be sorted into the category BAD.
~nPress the <%values.posLocation%> '<%values.pos_responsekey%>' <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> for GOOD.
press the <%values.negLocation%> '<%values.neg_responsekey%>' <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> for BAD.

A string of numbers and letters will act as a SIGNAL that the adjective is soon to appear. Both signal and adjective will appear right in the center of the screen.

This is a timed sorting task. GO AS FAST AS YOU CAN while making as few mistakes as possible. If you make a mistake a red X appears on screen.

Press the Spacebar to start a practice session."

/2 = "Practice is over and the actual task is about to start.
The actual task is just like the practice: you will see a signal that is followed by an adjective.
~nPress the <%values.posLocation%> '<%values.pos_responsekey%>' <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> for GOOD.
press the <%values.negLocation%> '<%values.neg_responsekey%>' <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> for BAD.

This is a timed sorting task. GO AS FAST AS YOU CAN while making as few mistakes as possible. If you make a mistake a red X appears on screen.

Press the Spacebar to start."
</item>

